  </p>

  <!-- YOUTUBE -->
  <h2>1. YouTube — How Nigerians Earn</h2>
  <p>YouTube is one of the highest-paying platforms for Nigerians.</p>

  <div class="guide-box">
    <h3>How to Earn on YouTube in Nigeria</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Create a YouTube channel in a profitable niche</li>
      <li>Upload videos consistently</li>
      <li>Reach 1,000 subscribers and 4,000 watch hours</li>
      <li>Apply for YouTube Monetization</li>
      <li>Earn from ads, brand deals, affiliate links, and memberships</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <!-- TIKTOK -->
  <h2>2. TikTok — How Nigerians Earn</h2>
  <p>TikTok allows Nigerians to earn even without the Creator Fund.</p>

  <div class="guide-box">
    <h3>How to Earn on TikTok in Nigeria</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Post engaging short videos daily</li>
      <li>Grow followers and engagement</li>
      <li>Join TikTok Live and receive gifts</li>
      <li>Promote affiliate products</li>
      <li>Earn commissions through TikTok Shop</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <!-- FACEBOOK -->
  <h2>3. Facebook — How Nigerians Earn</h2>
  <p>Facebook pays Nigerian creators through video monetization.</p>

  <div class="guide-box">
    <h3>How to Earn on Facebook in Nigeria</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Create a Facebook Page</li>
      <li>Post original video content</li>
      <li>Meet in-stream ads eligibility</li>
      <li>Earn from ad breaks and Stars</li>
      <li>Work with brands for sponsored posts</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <!-- MUSIC -->
  <h2>4. Music Platforms — How Nigerian Artists Earn</h2>

  <div class="guide-box">
    <h3>How to Earn as a Musician in Nigeria</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Upload music to Audiomack and Boomplay</li>
      <li>Use distributors to get on Spotify</li>
      <li>Promote songs on social media</li>
      <li>Earn royalties from streams</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

